<span id="xv.iv.iv.xxxvii"></span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.xxxvii-p1"></span> <span id="page_460">p. 460</span>
<span id="xv.iv.iv.xxxvii-Page_460"></span><span class="c4"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.xxxvii-p1.1"></span>Canon XXXVI.  (Greek xxxix.)</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.xxxvii-p2"></span>That bishops or clergymen are not
to be ordained unless they have made all their family Christians.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.xxxvii-p3"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.xxxvii-p3.1"></span>None</span> shall be ordained bishop,
presbyters, or deacons before all the inmates of their houses shall have
become Catholic Christians.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.xxxvii-p4"></span><span class="c4"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.xxxvii-p4.1"></span>Notes.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.xxxvii-p5"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.xxxvii-p5.1"></span>Ancient Epitome of Canon XXXVI.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.xxxvii-p6"></span>He shall not be ordained who hath
not made all his household orthodox.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.xxxvii-p7"></span>This canon is Canon xvij. of the
Synod of Hippo, <span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.xxxvii-p7.1"></span>a.d.</span> 393.

